main event: An unidentified aerial object was observed on 6/12/70 at 6:55 p.m. in Wibly, Colorado.
interesting points: The object was described as round in shape, silver in color, and estimated to be about 30-40 feet in diameter.
The object was moving at a moderate speed and was observed for about 5-10 minutes.
The object appeared to be larger than a star, slightly bright and slightly diamond shaped.
The object suddenly accelerated and disappeared.
The sighting was reported to the Air Force for investigation.
